1
00:00:11,833 --> 00:00:13,467
<i> Hurry up! Faster!</i>

2
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:14,733
<i> Emma!</i>

3
00:00:14,867 --> 00:00:16,500
<i> Stick to your clingy woman!</i>

4
00:00:16,633 --> 00:00:21,033
<i>You're the first man
who made me happy.</i>

5
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:23,767
<i> Not just because you're cute.</i>

6
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:25,233
<i> What am I to you?</i>

7
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:26,633
<i> We're friends.</i>

8
00:00:26,767 --> 00:00:31,100
<i>Hey! Stop!
What are you doing?</i>

9
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:34,000
<i> They say you'll only realize</i>

10
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:36,300
<i>the value of what you had
once they're gone.</i>

11
00:00:36,433 --> 00:00:37,233
<i> I find it true.</i>

12
00:00:37,367 --> 00:00:38,600
<i> Why are you telling me that?</i>

13
00:00:38,733 --> 00:00:39,900
<i> I miss a lot about you.</i>

14
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,867
<i>What do you want?
You only want Mookie, right?</i>

15
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,200
<i> You already have Logan.</i>

16
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,233
<i>We have nothing left
to talk about.</i>

17
00:00:45,367 --> 00:00:46,400
<i> Dan.</i>

18
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:49,433
<i> Oh, my! I love this OOTD.</i>

19
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:51,433
<i>What's the inspiration
behind this?</i>

20
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:52,467
<i> Is there a baptismal event?</i>

21
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:54,100
<i> I'll just return to the room.</i>

22
00:01:32,267 --> 00:01:36,500
And you told Zayn,
"You're super, super cute!"

23
00:01:36,633 --> 00:01:38,733
Did I really say that?

24
00:01:38,867 --> 00:01:39,633
Yes, girl.

25
00:01:39,767 --> 00:01:43,333
You almost told him
you liked him.

26
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:49,367
I thought my hangover

27
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:51,533
was the worst thing that had
ever happened to me.

28
00:01:53,533 --> 00:01:56,033
But did I really
almost say that?

29
00:01:56,167 --> 00:01:57,100
Yes.

30
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:59,167
Don't you remember anything?

31
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,967
Nothing.

32
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:03,333
I wish the earth
would swallow me.

33
00:02:03,467 --> 00:02:05,733
Gosh.

34
00:02:05,867 --> 00:02:09,100
Speaking of the super,
super cute devil...

35
00:02:09,233 --> 00:02:11,767
I'll get the door.
You still have a hangover.

36
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:15,167
I wish I could have a hangover
and a visitor the next day, too.

37
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:20,333
- She's so good at teasing me.
- Come in.

38
00:02:20,467 --> 00:02:21,567
Where's Mookie?

39
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:22,433
She's there.

40
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:27,600
Hey, Zayn.

41
00:02:29,033 --> 00:02:30,667
Here. Take this.

42
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:33,167
They say this will cure
your hangover.

43
00:02:35,133 --> 00:02:36,700
Thank you.

44
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:40,867
- But it's heavy.
- Is it?

45
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,800
- Oh, sorry.
- Let's put it here.

46
00:02:42,933 --> 00:02:45,633
That's how heavy
my head is, too.

47
00:02:47,533 --> 00:02:49,767
My head hurts so badly.

48
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:52,100
Drink some of this.

49
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:00,800
There.

50
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:02,200
Thank you, Zayn.

51
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:04,000
Anytime, Mooks.

52
00:03:04,133 --> 00:03:07,233
Just don't make passing out
a habit.

53
00:03:07,367 --> 00:03:08,700
He said you're heavy.

54
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:11,700
Hey, I didn't say that.
Cai is so silly.

55
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:16,233
Mooks, I swear it's okay.
Promise.

56
00:03:16,367 --> 00:03:17,967
- Really?
- Is that so?

57
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:19,567
Stop making up stories.

58
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:20,733
For real?

59
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:24,033
I will throw this to you next.
Would you like that?

60
00:03:24,167 --> 00:03:25,300
I'm just kidding.

61
00:03:25,433 --> 00:03:26,367
It was just a joke.

62
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,567
You're lucky the coconut juice
is good.

63
00:03:30,733 --> 00:03:32,067
Thanks again, Zayn.

64
00:03:34,533 --> 00:03:38,767
Love, from now on, let's focus
on the happy memories.

65
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:41,900
Let's forget about our fights.

66
00:03:42,033 --> 00:03:43,067
Okay.

67
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:43,800
Promise?

68
00:03:43,967 --> 00:03:44,867
Yes.

69
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,133
Mister! Excuse me!
Can you take our photo?

70
00:03:48,267 --> 00:03:50,033
Thank you.

71
00:03:50,167 --> 00:03:51,400
Okay. Come on.

72
00:03:57,933 --> 00:04:00,167
Hello? Excuse me?

73
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:01,267
Hello!

74
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,333
- Hello!
- Mister.

75
00:04:02,467 --> 00:04:04,300
<i>Mister, what's going on
with you?</i>

76
00:04:13,367 --> 00:04:14,067
Emma?

77
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,467
<i> Sorry, Ma'am.</i>

78
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,067
<i> One...</i>

79
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,033
Never mind.

80
00:04:26,167 --> 00:04:27,100
We're good.

81
00:04:29,033 --> 00:04:30,467
What's wrong with you?

82
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,567
Why?

83
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:33,700
Seriously? With all the routes
you could take,

84
00:04:33,833 --> 00:04:35,300
you had to pass by here?

85
00:04:35,433 --> 00:04:37,867
Sorry, you're blocking the way.

86
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:38,600
Emma!

87
00:04:41,033 --> 00:04:42,033
Love!

88
00:04:42,167 --> 00:04:44,600
Love, it hurts!

89
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:46,133
Damn, girl!

90
00:04:46,267 --> 00:04:47,133
Logan!

91
00:04:47,267 --> 00:04:48,533
Let's swim?

92
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:51,633
Come on.

93
00:04:51,767 --> 00:04:54,033
- Massage my back. It hurts.
- Here?

94
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,833
Focus on my back!

95
00:04:58,967 --> 00:05:00,733
- You're so distracted!
- Okay, come on.

96
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:11,100
Is it okay now?

97
00:05:13,933 --> 00:05:17,733
- Let's go!
- Okay, let's go. Come on!

98
00:05:17,867 --> 00:05:19,400
Let's stay here, okay?

99
00:05:19,533 --> 00:05:21,133
Come on!

100
00:05:21,267 --> 00:05:23,133
I don't want to.
That part is deep.

101
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:25,867
<i> Emma!</i>

102
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:32,067
Emma, that part is deep.

103
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:32,867
Hey!

104
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:36,833
- Come on! Hurry up!
- Come back here!

105
00:05:36,967 --> 00:05:38,333
Come here!

106
00:05:38,467 --> 00:05:39,833
You're so stubborn.

107
00:05:41,733 --> 00:05:42,867
Let's race. Come on!

108
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:43,833
I don't want to.

109
00:05:43,967 --> 00:05:46,533
I'm nervous for you.

110
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,233
Don't worry,
I won't get drowned.

111
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:51,067
The one who taught me was great.

112
00:05:52,100 --> 00:05:53,600
Was it Danilo?

113
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,100
Let's go, Love.

114
00:05:56,233 --> 00:05:57,967
Let's just go to the spa.

115
00:05:58,100 --> 00:05:59,700
The vibe here is getting bad.

116
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,767
You can go ahead, Jade.
I don't want a massage.

117
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:05,800
Why?

118
00:06:05,933 --> 00:06:08,633
I heard they have
good therapists.

119
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:12,000
We'll be relieved
of our unwanted stress.

120
00:06:12,133 --> 00:06:12,767
Let's go!

121
00:06:14,867 --> 00:06:16,933
No, I'll stay.

122
00:06:17,067 --> 00:06:18,800
Where are you going?

123
00:06:18,933 --> 00:06:20,567
I'll catch some fresh air.

124
00:06:22,467 --> 00:06:23,100
What?

125
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:25,100
Love!

126
00:06:32,167 --> 00:06:35,267
<i> Emma! Won't you really stop?</i>

127
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:04,033
Who are you looking for?

128
00:07:04,167 --> 00:07:06,867
Danilo won't come back.

129
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,767
I'm sure he's furious
because we're together.

130
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,100
Your moves are great.

131
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:14,500
They are effective.

132
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:17,033
But I'm a loser.

133
00:07:17,167 --> 00:07:18,400
You're using me too much.

134
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:20,467
I didn't intend to do that.

135
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:21,833
It's okay.

136
00:07:21,967 --> 00:07:23,367
I'm not complaining.

137
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,767
Use me whenever you want.

138
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:28,333
And I'm annoyed at Jade.

139
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:30,133
I want to get even with her.

140
00:07:30,267 --> 00:07:32,867
You no longer have feelings
for Danilo.

141
00:07:34,033 --> 00:07:34,967
Right?

142
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:38,467
Why can't you say anything?

143
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:42,133
Come on, Logan. Of course.

144
00:07:42,267 --> 00:07:44,733
I no longer have feelings
for Danilo.

145
00:07:44,867 --> 00:07:47,400
Sir Logan, you have a phone call
at the reception.

146
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:49,100
Okay, tell them I'll be there.

147
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:51,500
I have to go.

148
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:09,433
Mookie.

149
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:14,200
Dear, are you alone?

150
00:08:14,333 --> 00:08:16,867
Where are Zayn
and your other friend?

151
00:08:18,267 --> 00:08:20,267
Do you want me to stay with you?

152
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:21,800
Come on, let's swim.

153
00:08:21,967 --> 00:08:22,833
I'll teach you.

154
00:08:22,967 --> 00:08:24,200
No need.

155
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:26,233
I already know how to swim.

156
00:08:26,367 --> 00:08:28,267
Mommy Jade taught me.

157
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:34,400
She taught me many things,
like how to be independent.

158
00:08:34,533 --> 00:08:39,600
Important things that a mother
should be teaching me.

159
00:08:39,733 --> 00:08:41,233
So, it's okay.

160
00:08:41,367 --> 00:08:42,567
Excuse me.

161
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:43,733
Mookie.

162
00:08:43,867 --> 00:08:45,467
Mookie, dear.

163
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,933
What is it?

164
00:08:48,067 --> 00:08:49,533
What else do you want?

165
00:08:49,667 --> 00:08:52,100
Didn't I tell you
to stay away from me?

166
00:08:52,233 --> 00:08:53,467
Mookie, it's you I want.

167
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:56,400
I want us to talk.

168
00:08:56,533 --> 00:08:57,633
I want us to reconcile.

169
00:08:57,767 --> 00:09:00,900
I want us to continue
the family we've built.

170
00:09:01,033 --> 00:09:04,333
I suffered for 17 years
when you went missing.

171
00:09:04,467 --> 00:09:06,967
My heart was dead for 17 years.

172
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,533
It came back to life
when I found you.

173
00:09:10,667 --> 00:09:11,667
Dear...

174
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:14,400
Dear, I can't bear it
if I lose you again.

175
00:09:16,067 --> 00:09:18,100
But we still got separated.

176
00:09:19,133 --> 00:09:21,200
Because you left us.

177
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:22,833
So, please!

178
00:09:22,967 --> 00:09:24,833
Stay away from us!

179
00:09:24,967 --> 00:09:26,367
You already have Logan.

180
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,600
And we already have Mommy Jade.

181
00:09:28,767 --> 00:09:29,667
Dear.

182
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,333
Please don't push me away.

183
00:09:32,467 --> 00:09:35,367
Let me tell you
what really happened.

184
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:37,700
Why I couldn't go back
to you and your dad.

185
00:09:38,733 --> 00:09:40,900
Dear, please listen to me.

186
00:09:43,267 --> 00:09:44,167
Please stop.

187
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,833
It's too late for that.

188
00:10:09,067 --> 00:10:10,233
Oh no!

189
00:10:10,967 --> 00:10:11,733
Are you okay?

190
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:13,967
Oh, dear.

191
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:16,767
You're so clumsy.

192
00:10:17,067 --> 00:10:19,833
You're lucky I'm here.
I have quick reflexes.

193
00:10:19,967 --> 00:10:21,200
I was able to help you
right away.

194
00:10:21,333 --> 00:10:23,333
Especially since no one saw you.

195
00:10:23,467 --> 00:10:25,633
I'm lucky you're here?

196
00:10:25,767 --> 00:10:26,867
If I had known,

197
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,600
you poured something where
I'd walk just to make me slip.

198
00:10:29,733 --> 00:10:30,867
You really are evil!

199
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,267
Wow.

200
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,833
It's so rich coming from you.

201
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,200
If I'm a demon,

202
00:10:37,433 --> 00:10:39,033
and so are you.

203
00:10:39,167 --> 00:10:41,600
Because we came from
the same mother.

204
00:10:41,733 --> 00:10:43,833
Satan's mistress.

205
00:10:43,967 --> 00:10:46,000
Leave mom out of it!

206
00:10:46,133 --> 00:10:46,733
Why?

207
00:10:47,967 --> 00:10:50,133
Didn't you take after her?

208
00:10:50,267 --> 00:10:54,167
You're a negligent mother
like her.

209
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:55,233
I'm not a negligent mother!

210
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:56,400
No?

211
00:10:56,533 --> 00:10:59,467
You left Mookie
to be with your lover.

212
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,033
I didn't leave her!

213
00:11:01,167 --> 00:11:03,667
You did everything you could
to drive me out of my family

214
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,100
so you could steal them from me!

215
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:06,900
Let me go!
You're really shameless!

216
00:11:07,033 --> 00:11:08,333
- You're worse!
- Let me go!

217
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,267
You make nothing but trouble!

218
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,733
Darn you!

219
00:11:11,867 --> 00:11:13,067
Come here!

220
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,000
You're really shameless!

221
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,300
You're way out of line!

222
00:11:28,267 --> 00:11:30,233
Emma! What's going on?

223
00:11:30,367 --> 00:11:34,500
Emma! Stop! That's enough!

224
00:11:34,633 --> 00:11:39,367
I said stop! Emma, stop!

225
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:40,300
Trash!

226
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:42,300
I said that's enough!
Stop. Enough.

227
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:45,033
- Are you giving up?
- Are you okay?

228
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:46,767
<i> Someone's drowning!</i>

229
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,467
Help!

230
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:51,667
Mookie!

231
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:52,667
That's Mookie!

232
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,800
Mookie!

233
00:11:57,433 --> 00:11:58,533
<i> Oh no! Help!</i>

234
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:10,833
Mookie!

235
00:12:10,967 --> 00:12:13,033
Flor, ask for help!

236
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:16,267
Flor!

237
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,500
Why? What's happening?

238
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:21,200
Mookie drowned! Help them!
Hurry up!

239
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:22,633
<i> Mookie!</i>

240
00:12:22,767 --> 00:12:23,400
Emma!

241
00:12:23,533 --> 00:12:24,433
What happened to Mookie?

242
00:12:24,567 --> 00:12:28,167
Let's bring her to the clinic!
Hurry!

243
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:29,100
Mookie, dear!

244
00:12:29,233 --> 00:12:29,933
Mookie!

245
00:12:37,367 --> 00:12:38,733
Flor, please help me.

246
00:12:41,667 --> 00:12:43,233
Mookie, dear!

247
00:12:43,367 --> 00:12:45,133
Let's bring her to the clinic!
Come on!

248
00:12:51,367 --> 00:12:52,067
Emma.

249
00:12:53,233 --> 00:12:55,067
Put this on.
I got it by the pool.

250
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:55,933
Thank you.

251
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:56,700
You might be feeling cold
already.

252
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:06,600
Emma, don't worry.

253
00:13:06,867 --> 00:13:08,600
Our daughter is safe now.

254
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:10,067
And you saved her.

255
00:13:11,267 --> 00:13:13,200
Dan, we're still not sure.

256
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:15,500
What if water got into
her lungs?

257
00:13:15,633 --> 00:13:16,733
What if she suffers
from an infection?

258
00:13:16,867 --> 00:13:17,800
Or pneumonia?

259
00:13:17,933 --> 00:13:19,000
Wait.

260
00:13:19,133 --> 00:13:20,967
Why do you know such things?

261
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:24,800
I underwent first-aid training.
And even the staff of the bar.

262
00:13:24,967 --> 00:13:28,167
Dan, I'm scared of what could
happen to Mookie.

263
00:13:30,633 --> 00:13:33,233
Emma, don't worry.

264
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:35,733
Our daughter is brave.

265
00:13:37,333 --> 00:13:40,100
She'll get through this. Okay?

266
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,600
- Danilo?
- Jade.

267
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:56,000
Love!

268
00:13:57,500 --> 00:14:00,133
I was so worried when I heard
what happened to Mookie.

269
00:14:00,267 --> 00:14:01,433
How is she?

270
00:14:01,567 --> 00:14:03,667
Well. She's okay.

271
00:14:04,733 --> 00:14:06,100
Dad.

272
00:14:06,233 --> 00:14:07,467
Mookie. Dear.

273
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:08,867
It's okay, Emma.

274
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,600
I can take it from here.

275
00:14:10,733 --> 00:14:12,333
You can go now.

276
00:14:12,467 --> 00:14:14,567
I'm not leaving.

277
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:16,167
Why?

278
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:17,300
What would you do?

279
00:14:18,433 --> 00:14:19,467
Are you going to make a scene?

280
00:14:21,067 --> 00:14:23,133
Do you think Mookie
likes you to be here?

281
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:25,967
You no longer have
any right here, Emma.

282
00:14:28,667 --> 00:14:29,600
You can go.

283
00:14:31,433 --> 00:14:33,667
Emma, let's just go.

284
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,533
You and Jade might start
a fight.

285
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:37,500
Mookie might hate you even more.

286
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:46,933
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

287
00:14:47,067 --> 00:14:48,067
Flor.

288
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,333
Mookie.

289
00:14:54,467 --> 00:14:55,767
Baby girl.

290
00:14:55,900 --> 00:14:57,467
How are you feeling?

291
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,100
How are you, baby girl?

292
00:15:01,267 --> 00:15:03,967
- I'm okay.
- Don't worry.

293
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:06,200
Everything is normal
with Mookie.

294
00:15:07,267 --> 00:15:08,833
I'm glad to hear that.

295
00:15:08,967 --> 00:15:09,900
<i> Thank you, Doc.</i>

296
00:15:10,033 --> 00:15:10,900
Thank you.

297
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:14,767
I'm so glad you're safe, Mookie.

298
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:21,933
Where's mom?

299
00:15:23,467 --> 00:15:25,367
She saved me, right?

300
00:15:27,667 --> 00:15:31,067
She was here earlier, Mookie.

301
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,800
She waited for you to wake up.

302
00:15:32,933 --> 00:15:34,333
But she already left.

303
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:37,233
Logan took her way.

304
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:38,800
I think they're going somewhere.

305
00:15:38,933 --> 00:15:41,267
They have a date or something.

306
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:43,067
Anyway, Mookie, don't worry.

307
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,267
I'm here for you.

308
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:50,267
And I will never leave you
for anyone.

309
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,267
Okay, baby girl?

310
00:16:05,733 --> 00:16:06,533
Mookie, I'm sorry.

311
00:16:06,667 --> 00:16:08,700
I wasn't there for you.

312
00:16:08,867 --> 00:16:10,100
Sorry, bestie.

313
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:12,567
We weren't there.

314
00:16:12,700 --> 00:16:13,900
Come on, guys.

315
00:16:14,033 --> 00:16:15,167
It's okay.

316
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:17,333
No one wanted that to happen.

317
00:16:18,367 --> 00:16:20,433
We still should have come
with you.

318
00:16:20,567 --> 00:16:22,533
What if Aunt Emma wasn't there?

319
00:16:22,667 --> 00:16:24,033
You could have drowned.

320
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:28,233
You know what, guys?

321
00:16:28,367 --> 00:16:31,433
I think it's better to stop
talking about what happened.

322
00:16:31,567 --> 00:16:34,733
Let's just focus on preparing
for the main event tomorrow.

323
00:16:34,867 --> 00:16:38,300
Baby girl, it's okay
if we still do that, right?

324
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:45,267
Jade, maybe it's better if
we cancel the activity tomorrow.

325
00:16:45,433 --> 00:16:50,633
A lot of trouble has already
happened since we arrived.

326
00:16:51,233 --> 00:16:56,000
I want Mookie to rest at home.

327
00:16:56,133 --> 00:16:57,033
What?

328
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:00,700
But that's the reason
we're here!

329
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:02,167
For that photo shoot!

330
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:08,933
It's such a waste
of the photographer's

331
00:17:09,067 --> 00:17:11,133
and the whole team's efforts.

332
00:17:11,267 --> 00:17:14,600
They thought about the concept
carefully.

333
00:17:16,667 --> 00:17:18,633
But you're right, Love.

334
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:22,400
Mookie should rest at home.

335
00:17:23,767 --> 00:17:33,733
So, I'll call the team to cancel
the shoot tomorrow.

336
00:17:54,133 --> 00:17:58,200
Emma! Hey! Where are you going?
Stay here. Come on.

337
00:18:00,233 --> 00:18:01,833
What the hell
are you doing here?

338
00:18:03,167 --> 00:18:04,433
I'll just see how my daughter
is doing.

339
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:08,700
Is it really Mookie
you want to see?

340
00:18:08,833 --> 00:18:12,067
Or do you plan to seduce
my fiancé again?

341
00:18:13,367 --> 00:18:15,200
I don't care about Danilo.

342
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:16,900
I only care about Mookie.

343
00:18:17,033 --> 00:18:19,600
Well, Mookie's fine.

344
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:22,600
You can go now.

345
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:26,667
What?

346
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:30,300
What are you waiting for?

347
00:18:30,433 --> 00:18:33,267
Are you going to listen
while we do our thing?

348
00:18:34,700 --> 00:18:35,267
Go!

349
00:18:38,633 --> 00:18:39,567
Let's go.

350
00:18:46,567 --> 00:18:48,633
Mooks, tell me. What's wrong?

351
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:51,467
Nothing.

352
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:54,533
It's just that...

353
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:55,900
you know...

354
00:18:56,033 --> 00:18:59,767
mom didn't even show up
after saving me.

355
00:19:01,967 --> 00:19:03,133
It's okay, Mooks.

356
00:19:07,067 --> 00:19:11,633
I want to thank her.

357
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:16,967
But I think she and Logan
are busy.

358
00:19:17,100 --> 00:19:17,767
What?

359
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:20,633
I talked to Flor.

360
00:19:20,767 --> 00:19:22,400
Aunt Jade is stopping her.

361
00:19:22,533 --> 00:19:23,700
She doesn't want your mom
to get near you.

362
00:19:24,867 --> 00:19:25,667
What?

363
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:29,500
Zayn, please come with me.

364
00:19:29,667 --> 00:19:31,067
Let's go to mom.

365
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,700
Mooks, you need to rest.

366
00:19:33,967 --> 00:19:37,067
Mooks, he's right.
You need to rest.

367
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:38,533
No, I'm okay.

368
00:19:39,267 --> 00:19:43,700
I must talk to mom
and thank her.

369
00:20:06,467 --> 00:20:07,600
Danilo.

370
00:20:10,833 --> 00:20:11,833
You know...

371
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:14,867
a lot of trouble
has been happening here

372
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,000
because of you and Jade.

373
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:19,567
Why don't you bring
your woman home?

374
00:20:20,100 --> 00:20:22,333
You're the ones who started
this mess.

375
00:20:22,467 --> 00:20:23,500
Like now.

376
00:20:25,033 --> 00:20:27,500
Leave Emma alone.

377
00:20:27,633 --> 00:20:30,800
Focus on your girlfriend.

378
00:20:30,933 --> 00:20:32,967
We have a daughter.

379
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:35,867
It's unavoidable that Emma
and I will talk.

380
00:20:36,033 --> 00:20:39,567
And it's none of your business
if Emma wants to talk to me.

381
00:20:39,700 --> 00:20:40,833
Oh, really?

382
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:53,300
What now?

383
00:20:53,433 --> 00:20:55,100
Danilo, what are you doing?

384
00:20:55,233 --> 00:20:57,067
- Bring him to the clinic!
- Can you stop that?

385
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,933
What's going on with you?

386
00:21:02,533 --> 00:21:05,967
What are you doing?
Why are you fighting with Logan?

387
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:07,733
Is it because of Emma again?

388
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:09,200
Why?

389
00:21:09,367 --> 00:21:10,667
Are you jealous?

390
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:13,067
Jealous? I'm not jealous.

391
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,333
This isn't going anywhere.

392
00:21:15,467 --> 00:21:18,867
Let's just talk
when we've both cooled down.

393
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:22,467
Danilo, wait!

394
00:21:37,633 --> 00:21:38,700
Hello, Caloy.

395
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:42,767
Where's the person I told you
to find?

396
00:21:42,933 --> 00:21:44,533
Baldo!

397
00:21:44,667 --> 00:21:46,533
Is he here already?

398
00:21:46,667 --> 00:21:47,433
<i> Yes, Ma'am.</i>

399
00:21:47,767 --> 00:21:49,100
<i> We've just talked.</i>

400
00:21:49,233 --> 00:21:50,600
<i> He told me he had seen you.</i>

401
00:21:50,733 --> 00:21:52,933
<i>But he's not approaching you
because someone might see him.</i>

402
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:56,900
Tell him to come here
at the back of the resort,

403
00:21:57,033 --> 00:21:58,900
by the tree with a stair.

404
00:21:59,033 --> 00:21:59,967
Now.

405
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:02,000
We'll talk here.

406
00:22:11,667 --> 00:22:12,600
Are you Baldo?

407
00:22:12,733 --> 00:22:13,367
Yes, Ma'am.

408
00:22:14,467 --> 00:22:15,800
Here's your target.

409
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:19,900
Her?

410
00:22:20,033 --> 00:22:22,700
<i>Caloy showed her to me
when we talked.</i>

411
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:24,700
What do you want me to do
to her?

412
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:27,267
Should I kidnap her?
Or scare her?

413
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:30,433
I don't care what you'll do
to her.

414
00:22:30,667 --> 00:22:35,800
What matters is to take her away
from this resort.

415
00:22:35,933 --> 00:22:38,567
Because she's getting
on my nerves.

416
00:22:59,867 --> 00:23:00,600
Zayn.

417
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:04,267
I will call the wedding off!

418
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,800
Don't do this to me, Danilo!

419
00:23:05,933 --> 00:23:08,667
We need to stop them
from getting back together.

420
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:09,967
What's your plan?

421
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:12,533
Olive will do anything...

422
00:23:12,667 --> 00:23:15,067
Mr. Driver, go! Chase them!

423
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:18,033
to ruin Emma's family.

424
00:23:18,167 --> 00:23:20,467
No.

425
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:21,967
Things are going well
for Emma now.

426
00:23:22,133 --> 00:23:23,733
But you're messing
with everything again.

427
00:23:23,867 --> 00:23:25,233
I'm not scared of you.

428
00:23:25,367 --> 00:23:27,967
I can totally match
your badness.
